document_data.name: Beef Sharburg
document_data.mainbody: '''''Beef Sharburg''''' was an exquisite and expensive dish that originated from [[Sharburg]] in the [[Dalelands]].
document_data.Description: Beef Sharburg was a complex dish, served with a side of [[Marsember]] [[beet]]s and followed up with a bowl of [[eldritch berry custard]].
document_data.History: Even though originated in the Dalelands, Beef Sharburg was served in more exclusive and expensive inns, such as [[Chateau Elite]] in [[Daggerford]] ''circa'' [[1372 DR]].
